cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with machine learning classifiers and their ability to recognize new concepts with limited data without re-training on the full training set. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also deals with image classification, which is covered by the sub-category cs.CV. The paper uses attention mechanisms, which are covered by the sub-category cs.CL. Finally, the paper proposes a meta-learning model, which is covered by the sub-category cs.NE.
